org.jlibsedml

Class Libsedml

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.jlibsedml.Libsedml

  • public class Libsedml
extends Object
    Provides an entry point to the SedML object model. To read a SED-ML file, 
     SEDMLDocument doc = Libsedml.readDocument(myFile);
 // get errors
 List<SedMLError> errors = doc.getErrors();
 
 // Alternatively, if you're creating a SED-ML document from scratch, do
 doc = LibsedML.createDocument();
 // get model
 Sedml model = doc.getSedMLModel();
 
 // apply changes to your model using the SED-ML API
 
 // write document back to file
 doc.writeDocument(myFile);
 
 // to write a .sedx archive file with the model file included:
 
 List<IModelFile> models = new ArrayList<IModelFile>();
 models.add(new FileModelContent(myModelFile));
 ArchiveComponents comps = new ArchiveComponents(models, doc);
 
 byte[] zippedBytes = LibSedml.writeMiaseAchive(comps);
 
 // persist your zipped archive
    Since:
    1.0
    Author:
    Richard Adams

      • isSEDML

        public static boolean isSEDML(File file)
        Boolean test for whether a file is a SED-ML file or not.
        Parameters:
        file - A non-null, readable file.
        Returns:
        true if this is a SED-ML file (i.e., a readable XML file with the SED-ML namespace). If the XML cannot be parsed, or the root element namespace is not that of SED-ML, returns false.

        Parameters:
        inputStream - A non-null, readable InputStream.
        Returns:
        true if the input stream is to a a SED-ML resource (i.e., a readable XML with the SED-ML namespace). If the XML cannot be parsed, or the root element namespace is not SED-ML, returns false.

      • writeSEDMLArchive

        public static byte[] writeSEDMLArchive(ArchiveComponents components,
                                       String sedmlName)
                                throws XMLException
        Deprecated. - use OMEX /Combine archive format from now on - the sedx archive is obsolete.
        Generates a sedx archive of a SED-ML document and its constituent model files. Within the archive, the SED-ML document will called 'sedml.xml'
        Parameters:
        components - An ArchiveComponents object.
        sedmlName - A name for the SEDML component of the archive. This should be the same as the root of the name of the file to which the archive will be saved. E.g., if
        sedmlName is mysedml, then the entry in the archive will be :
        mysedml.xml
        and the final .sedx archive should be called mysedml.sedx
        Returns:
        A byte[] of the zipped contents, or null.
        Throws:
        XMLException - if any aspect of zipping could not be performed.

      • readSEDMLArchive

        public static ArchiveComponents readSEDMLArchive(InputStream archive)
                                          throws XMLException
        Reads an archive, which should be in sedx format - i.e., a zip archive containing a SED-ML file and possibly one or more model files.
        This method is kept for reading legacy archives, but the SEDML archive format is now superceded by the Combine archive format
        Parameters:
        archive - An InputStream onto the archive
        Returns:
        A non-null ArchiveComponents objects.
        Throws:
        XMLException
        {@link - IllegalArgumentException} if parameter File is null, unreadable, or does not end in ".sedx".

      • parseFormulaString

        public static org.jmathml.ASTNode parseFormulaString(String math)
        Convenience method to parse free text math into an ASTNode. The style of math is a C-style syntax, e.g.,
        . The parsing supports standard arithmetical operations and function calls. E.g.,
        • 4 + 2
        • sin(pi / 2) // or any other trig function
        • log(9,81) // = 2
        • root(4,81) //=3
        • exp(t)

        In addition, the strings pi, NaN, infinity and exponentiale are translated into constants.

        Functions not supported by this library ( see ASTFunctionType for supported functions ) will be parsed into a function call, which will not be evaluable. E.g., 
         myfunction(a, b)
        can be turned into an ASTNode, but will not be evaluable, unless a symbol definition class is supplied. (See the org.jlibsedml.mathsymbols package for how the SED-ML aggregate functions are supported).
        Parameters:
        math - A String of math.
        Returns:
        An ASTNode. This will be an ASTRootNode with the math nodes as children. E.g., the string 
         2 * (4 / 5)
        will return the structure: 
          ASTRootNode
       ASTimes
            ASTCn(2)
            ASTDivide
                 ASTCn(4)
                 ASTCn(5)
        If math is null or empty, returns null.
        Throws:
        RuntimeException - if mathString cannot be parsed due to incorrect syntax.
